The paper deals with the problem of private information retrieval, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of cache in the PIR scheme involves storage and retrieval of data, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the capacity of the PIR scheme, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a memory-sharing based PIR scheme, which involves the sharing of resources and is a topic in systems and networking (cs.SI).
